Brazil Holds Livestock Exhibition 
The biggest livestock and farm machinery exhibition in Latin America
opened today in Porto Alegre, the capital of the Brazilian state of Rio
Grande do Sul.
The fair has attracted 1,500 exhibitors and 200 farm machinery
companies from 15 Latin American and European countries.
As many as 5,000 animals such as horses, cattle, sheep and goats are
displayed at the exhibition.
Rio Grande do Sul Agriculture Secretary Cesar Schirmer said that more
than one million people could visit the fair and business transactions
are likely to surpass last year's.
The exhibition will close on September 3.
